My Business Experience

At the age of 12 years old I was blessed to be hired as a real estate secretary at one of my neighbor's real estate office. He taught me everything about real estate, advertising and what it took to have a successful business. I worked there until I was 18 years old. From there I became a paralegal. Started working for a major law firm NYC. Then worked for law firms in NJ specializing in Real Estate and family law until I was 25 years old. I then worked about a year and half selling cars. I had started studying consistently natural medicine at the age of 10 years old. At 27 years old I was blessed to meet this wonderful woman who was a Ayurvedic physcian/surgeon. She was teaching a ayurvedic class that I attend. She saw something special in me and graciously offered a one on one internship with her that lasted for 5 years. During this time, after leaving sales, I had opened a Natural Medicine practice. Here I offered spiritual coaching, nutritional coaching and massage therapy. Through this business not only was I blessed to heal so many but through this process I gained so much more knowledge. I am now ready and excited for my journey into the software engineering experience.
